<subSubSection id="A4A011E5FFBF6A23F28B7341FE3DFDC9" lastPageId="41" lastPageNumber="42" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="description">
<paragraph id="EC05426EFFBF6A22F28B7341FEDCF90F" blockId="40.[151,1436,1322,2028]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBF6A22F28B7341FEC4FACF" bold="true" box="[151,303,1322,1348]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBF6A22F3267340FDDCFACF" box="[314,567,1323,1348]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">External morphology</emphasis>
: Shell reduced, 2.5–2.7 whorls, glossy, spire and apex flattened. Protoconch smooth (
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBF6A22F3527338FDF2FAE7" box="[334,537,1363,1388]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Peloparion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="iridis">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBF6A22F3527338FDF2FAE7" box="[334,537,1363,1388]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Peloparion iridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or sculptured with incised spiral grooves (
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBF6A22F63E7338FB77FAE7" authorityName="Godwin-Austen" authorityYear="1883" box="[1058,1180,1363,1388]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Helicarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="helenae">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBF6A22F63E7338FB77FAE7" box="[1058,1180,1363,1388]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">P. helenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); teleoconch smooth. Whorl profile rounded above and below evenly convex periphery. Internal walls of early whorls complete; umbilicus closed. Right mantle lap large, rounded; left mantle lap moderately small, rounded (
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBF6A22F70E73C8FA84FA37" box="[1298,1391,1443,1468]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Peloparion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="iridis">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBF6A22F70E73C8FA84FA37" box="[1298,1391,1443,1468]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">P. iridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or tapering to a slight point (
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBF6A22F3D873A0FDD0FA6F" authorityName="Godwin-Austen" authorityYear="1883" box="[452,571,1483,1508]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Helicarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="helenae">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBF6A22F3D873A0FDD0FA6F" box="[452,571,1483,1508]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">P. helenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); mantle laps fused at base, right mantle lap with dark border around edge and left mantle lap with dark stripe through middle, both laps with dark spots. Mantle lobes small to medium, median and left lobe fused. Sides of body and mantle laps and lobes covered with tiny specks of pale pigment iridescent in life in 
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBF6A22F3607028FE3CF9D7" box="[380,471,1603,1628]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Peloparion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="iridis">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBF6A22F3607028FE3CF9D7" box="[380,471,1603,1628]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">P. iridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBF6A22F3F47028FD8BF9D7" authorityName="Godwin-Austen" authorityYear="1883" box="[488,608,1603,1628]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Helicarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="helenae">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBF6A22F3F47028FD8BF9D7" box="[488,608,1603,1628]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">P. helenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
not examined alive). Caudal apparatus as for genus; caudal foss vertical slit in tail.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EC05426EFFBF6A22F2DF70F8FABBF927" blockId="40.[151,1436,1322,2028]" box="[195,1360,1682,1708]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBF6A22F2DF70F8FE88F927" box="[195,355,1683,1708]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Mantle cavity</emphasis>
: As for family. Mantle with visible minor blood vessels; pigmentation of white spots.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EC05426EFFBF6A22F2DF70D0FD26F95F" blockId="40.[151,1436,1322,2028]" box="[195,717,1722,1748]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBF6A22F2DF70D0FE6CF95F" box="[195,391,1723,1748]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Digestive system</emphasis>
: Oesophageal crop present.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EC05426EFFBF6A23F2DF7088FD24FEF1" blockId="40.[151,1436,1322,2028]" lastBlockId="41.[151,1436,152,1578]" lastPageId="41" lastPageNumber="42" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBF6A22F2DF7088FE9FF977" box="[195,372,1763,1788]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Genital system</emphasis>
: As for family. Carrefour and talon both embedded in albumen gland. Free oviduct of medium length; capsular gland present; internal longitudinal pilasters absent. Bursa copulatrix inserted on vagina, short (less than half spermoviduct length) in 
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBF6A22F11D7158FC92F8C7" authorityName="Godwin-Austen" authorityYear="1883" box="[769,889,1843,1868]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Helicarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="helenae">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBF6A22F11D7158FC92F8C7" box="[769,889,1843,1868]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">P.helenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, or moderately short (about half spermoviduct length) in 
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBF6A22F3137130FE81F8FF" box="[271,362,1883,1908]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Peloparion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="iridis">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBF6A22F3137130FE81F8FF" box="[271,362,1883,1908]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">P. iridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; duct of bursa copulatrix wide (
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBF6A22F0FF7130FCD6F8FF" box="[739,829,1883,1908]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Peloparion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="iridis">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBF6A22F0FF7130FCD6F8FF" box="[739,829,1883,1908]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">P. iridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or narrow (
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBF6A22F1CF7130FBA0F8FF" authorityName="Godwin-Austen" authorityYear="1883" box="[979,1099,1883,1908]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Helicarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="helenae">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBF6A22F1CF7130FBA0F8FF" box="[979,1099,1883,1908]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">P. helenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), distinguishable from bursa copulatrix, internally with longitudinal pilasters. Vagina internally with longitudinal pilasters. Epiphallus enters penis through simple pore (
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBF6A22F03B71C0FD69F84F" box="[551,642,1963,1988]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Peloparion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="iridis">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBF6A22F03B71C0FD69F84F" box="[551,642,1963,1988]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">P. iridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or a medium length verge (
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBF6A22F1CD71C0FBA3F84F" authorityName="Godwin-Austen" authorityYear="1883" box="[977,1096,1963,1988]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Helicarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="helenae">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBF6A22F1CD71C0FBA3F84F" box="[977,1096,1963,1988]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">P. helenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); penis internally smooth (
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBF6A22F79A71C0FF19F867" authorityName="Godwin-Austen" authorityYear="1883" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Helicarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="helenae">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBF6A22F79A71C0FF19F867" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">P. helenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or covered in faint longitudinal ridges (
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBF6A22F0C471B8FCDFF867" box="[728,820,2003,2028]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Peloparion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="iridis">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBF6A22F0C471B8FCDFF867" box="[728,820,2003,2028]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">P. iridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), longitudinal penis pilasters present, circular pilasters also present in 
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F36776F3FE18FF3A" authorityName="Godwin-Austen" authorityYear="1883" box="[379,499,152,177]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Helicarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="helenae">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F36776F3FE18FF3A" box="[379,499,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">P. helenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, diverticulum on penis absent. Penial sheath enclosing only penis; penis retractor muscle attached to epiphallus. Epiphallus simple internally. Epiphallic retractor caecum absent. Flagellum present; flagellum and distal part of epiphallus with small internal cryptae forming external projections (
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F79A7683FF19FEA2" authorityName="Godwin-Austen" authorityYear="1883" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Helicarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="helenae">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F79A7683FF19FEA2" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">P. helenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), or with internal cryptae hidden by a thick external layer of muscle (
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F600777BFB9DFEA2" box="[1052,1142,272,297]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Peloparion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="iridis">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F600777BFB9DFEA2" box="[1052,1142,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">P. iridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Spermatophore (
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F74E777BFF25FEDA" authorityName="Godwin-Austen" authorityYear="1883" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Helicarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="helenae">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F74E777BFF25FEDA" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">P.helenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only) soft capsule with firm tail pipe open at one end, tail pipe moderately long, narrow, sculptured at base of capsule with few short branching spines.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EC05426EFFBE6A23F2DF77E3FE3DFDC9" blockId="41.[151,1436,152,1578]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F2DF77E3FE75FE29" authority=": Relatively" authorityName="Relatively" box="[195,414,392,418]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Radulaceae" genus="Radula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F2DF77E3FEFCFE2A" box="[195,279,392,417]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Radula</emphasis>
: Relatively
</taxonomicName>
long and narrow. Central tooth with small ectocones; mesocone longer than tooth base. Lateral and marginal tooth fields distinguishable. Lateral teeth with endocone smaller than central tooth ectocones; ectocone equal in size to those on central tooth; mesocone shorter than tooth base, or longer than tooth base. Marginal teeth with endocones absent; ectocones approximately same length and breadth as mesocone, subdivided into extra teeth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A4A011E5FFBE6A23F2DA7424FE00F9A1" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EC05426EFFBE6A23F2DA7424FC70FC09" blockId="41.[151,1436,152,1578]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F2DA7424FED4FDE2" bold="true" box="[198,319,591,617]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F35A743BFE21FDE2" authorityName="Iredale" authorityYear="1937" box="[326,458,592,617]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Peloparion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F35A743BFE21FDE2" box="[326,458,592,617]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Peloparion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was introduced as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F14E743BFC3AFDE2" baseAuthorityName="Iredale" baseAuthorityYear="1937" box="[850,977,592,617]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Helicarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F14E743BFC3AFDE2" box="[850,977,592,617]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Helicarion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for 
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F61D743BFAB3FDE1" authority="Pfeiffer, 1855" authorityName="Pfeiffer" authorityYear="1855" box="[1025,1368,592,618]" class="Gastropoda" family="Vitrinidae" genus="Vitrina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="hyalina">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F61D743BFB5AFDE2" box="[1025,1201,592,617]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Vitrina hyalina</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="882B3F9FFFBE6A23F6A4743BFAB3FDE1" author="Pfeiffer, L." box="[1208,1368,592,618]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" pagination="286 - 298" refId="ref76244" refString="Pfeiffer, L. (1855) Descriptions of fifty-seven new species of Helicea, from Mr Cuming's collection. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 1854, 286 - 298." type="journal article" year="1855">Pfeiffer, 1855</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(now 
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F28B7413FE61FD1A" baseAuthorityName="Pfeiffer" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[151,394,632,657]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Mysticarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="hyalina">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F28B7413FE61FD1A" box="[151,394,632,657]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Mysticarion hyalina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; see above), with 
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F0657413FB92FD19" authority="Godwin-Austen, 1883" authorityName="Godwin-Austen" authorityYear="1883" box="[633,1145,632,658]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Helicarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="helenae">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F0657413FC8AFD1A" box="[633,865,632,657]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Helicarion helenae</emphasis>
Godwin-Austen, 1883
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym (
<bibRefCitation id="882B3F9FFFBE6A23F7557413FF08FD31" author="Iredale, T." pageId="41" pageNumber="42" pagination="1 - 39" refId="ref75467" refString="Iredale, T. (1937 c) A basic list of the land Mollusca of Australia - part II. Australian Zoologist, 9, 1 - 39." type="journal article" year="1937">Iredale 1937c</bibRefCitation>
). Later 
<bibRefCitation id="882B3F9FFFBE6A23F32174CBFE0FFD31" author="Iredale, T." box="[317,484,672,698]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref75529" refString="Iredale, T. (1941) Guide to the land shells of New South Wales - part III. The Australian Naturalist, 11, 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="1941">Iredale (1941)</bibRefCitation>
separated the two species, stated that the new subgenus name had been intended for 
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F2D874A3FEF4FD6A" authorityName="Godwin-Austen" authorityYear="1883" box="[196,287,712,737]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Helicarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="helenae">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F2D874A3FEF4FD6A" box="[196,287,712,737]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">helenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, not 
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F37D74A3FE52FD6A" baseAuthorityName="Pfeiffer" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[353,441,712,737]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Mysticarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="hyalina">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F37D74A3FE52FD6A" box="[353,441,712,737]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">hyalina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and raised it to genus level, as well as describing a second species in the genus, 
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F28B749BFDA3FC81" authority="Iredale, 1941" authorityName="Iredale" authorityYear="1941" box="[151,584,752,778]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Peloparion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="submissus">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F28B749BFE77FC82" box="[151,412,752,777]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Peloparion submissus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="882B3F9FFFBE6A23F3BB749BFDA3FC81" author="Iredale, T." box="[423,584,752,778]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref75529" refString="Iredale, T. (1941) Guide to the land shells of New South Wales - part III. The Australian Naturalist, 11, 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="1941">Iredale, 1941</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Two species, 
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F0E0749BFC9CFC82" authorityName="Godwin-Austen" authorityYear="1883" box="[764,887,752,777]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Helicarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="helenae">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F0E0749BFC9CFC82" box="[764,887,752,777]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">P. helenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F1AB749BFBA4FC82" authorityName="Iredale" authorityYear="1941" box="[951,1103,752,777]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Peloparion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="submissus">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F1AB749BFBA4FC82" box="[951,1103,752,777]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">P. submissus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, were recognised by 
<bibRefCitation id="882B3F9FFFBE6A23F74A749BFF0FFCB9" author="Smith, B. J." pageId="41" pageNumber="42" pagination="408" refId="ref77207" refString="Smith, B. J. (1992) Non-marine Mollusca. In: Houston, W. W. K. (Ed.) Zoological Catalogue of Australia. Australian Government Publishing Service, Canberra, pp. 408." type="book chapter" year="1992">Smith (1992)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="882B3F9FFFBE6A23F3027573FDEBFCB9" author="Smith, B. J. &amp; Reid, S. &amp; Ponder, W. F." box="[286,512,792,818]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" refId="ref77380" refString="Smith, B. J., Reid, S. &amp; Ponder, W. F. (2002) Australian Faunal Directory, Mollusca: Pulmonata. Australian Biological Resources Study, http: // www. deh. gov. au / cgi-bin / abrs / abif-fauna / tree. pl? pstrVol = PULMONATA &amp; pintMode = 1." type="url" year="2002">
Smith 
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F3707573FE4DFCBA" box="[364,422,792,817]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">et al.</emphasis>
(2002)
</bibRefCitation>
. Hyman (2007) recognised that two different species were represented in 
<bibRefCitation id="882B3F9FFFBE6A23F77C7573FE7DFCD1" author="Godwin-Austen, H. H." pageId="41" pageNumber="42" refId="ref74602" refString="Godwin-Austen, H. H. (1883 b) Land and Freshwater Mollusca of India, Including South Arabia, Baluchistan, Afghanistan, Kashmir, Nepal, Burmah, Pegu, Tenasserim, Malay Peninsula, Ceylon, and Other Islands of the Indian Ocean. Part IV. Supplementary to Messrs. Theobald and Hanley's Conchologica Indica. Taylor and Francis, London." type="book" year="1883">Godwin-Austen’s (1883b)</bibRefCitation>
figures of 
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F008752BFD1EFCD2" authorityName="Godwin-Austen" authorityYear="1883" box="[532,757,832,857]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Helicarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="helenae">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F008752BFD1EFCD2" box="[532,757,832,857]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Helicarion helenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and consequently synonymised 
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F673752BFB06FCD2" authorityName="Godwin-Austen" authorityYear="1883" box="[1135,1261,832,857]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Helicarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="helenae">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F673752BFB06FCD2" box="[1135,1261,832,857]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">H. helenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F738752BFF57FC0A" authorityName="Iredale" authorityYear="1941" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Peloparion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="submissus">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F738752BFF57FC0A" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">P.submissus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and described a new species, 
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F0387503FC7CFC09" authority="Hyman, 2007" authorityName="Hyman, 2007 Semislug (Hyman" authorityYear="2007" box="[548,919,872,898]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Peloparion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="iridis">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F0387503FD06FC0A" box="[548,749,872,897]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Peloparion iridis</emphasis>
Hyman, 2007
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EC05426EFFBE6A23F2DF75FBFE51FC71" blockId="41.[151,1436,152,1578]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F2DF75FBFE41FC22" box="[195,426,912,937]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Peloparion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="helenae">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F2DF75FBFE41FC22" box="[195,426,912,937]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Peloparion helenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F3F975FBFD5BFC22" authorityName="Hyman, 2007 Semislug (Hyman" authorityYear="2007" box="[485,688,912,937]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Peloparion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="iridis">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F3F975FBFD5BFC22" box="[485,688,912,937]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Peloparion iridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were examined for the current study and the genus description below is based on both species. 
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F00875D3FD35FC5A" authorityName="Hyman, 2007 Semislug (Hyman" authorityYear="2007" box="[532,734,952,977]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Peloparion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="iridis">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F00875D3FD35FC5A" box="[532,734,952,977]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Peloparion iridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described in detail by Hyman (2007), so that information is not included here.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EC05426EFFBE6A23F2DF7263FBA0FB11" blockId="41.[151,1436,152,1578]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
Members of the genus are distinctive in having small, flattened, reduced shells of fewer than three whorls and a dark border surrounding the rounded mantle laps which are pigmented with dark spots. Specimens in ethanol have tiny specks of pale pigment on the mantle laps and lobes and on the body which are iridescent in living 
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F2FF72EBFED6FB12" authorityName="Hyman, 2007 Semislug (Hyman" authorityYear="2007" box="[227,317,1152,1177]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Peloparion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="iridis">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F2FF72EBFED6FB12" box="[227,317,1152,1177]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">P. iridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(only visible under magnification; 
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F0C772EBFCB8FB12" box="[731,851,1152,1177]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Peloparion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="helenae">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F0C772EBFCB8FB12" box="[731,851,1152,1177]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">P. helenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
not examined alive).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EC05426EFFBE6A23F2DF72C3FE00F9A1" blockId="41.[151,1436,152,1578]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F2DF72C3FEACFB4A" authorityName="Iredale" authorityYear="1937" box="[195,327,1192,1217]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Peloparion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F2DF72C3FEACFB4A" box="[195,327,1192,1217]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Peloparion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the other southeast Australian genera (
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F1D972C3FBAFFB4A" baseAuthorityName="Iredale" baseAuthorityYear="1937" box="[965,1092,1192,1217]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Helicarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F1D972C3FBAFFB4A" box="[965,1092,1192,1217]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Helicarion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F64A72C3FB08FB4A" authorityName="Iredale" authorityYear="1941" box="[1110,1251,1192,1217]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Mysticarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F64A72C3FB08FB4A" box="[1110,1251,1192,1217]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Mysticarion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F6EB72C3FA7EFB4A" authorityName="Iredale" authorityYear="1937" box="[1271,1429,1192,1217]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Parmavitrina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F6EB72C3FA7EFB4A" box="[1271,1429,1192,1217]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Parmavitrina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F28B72BBFEF3FB62" authorityName="Hyman" authorityYear="2007" box="[151,280,1232,1257]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Brevisentis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F28B72BBFEF3FB62" box="[151,280,1232,1257]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Brevisentis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in the shape of the flagellum and the spermatophore, although the latter structure was only observed in 
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F3397293FE76FA9A" box="[293,413,1272,1297]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Peloparion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="helenae">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F3397293FE76FA9A" box="[293,413,1272,1297]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">P. helenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A close examination reveals internal cryptae in the flagellum and/or the distal epiphallus in both species, indicating that their spermatophores have spines. However, the cryptae are not visible from the outside of the flagellum, as they are in all the other southeast Australian genera. This is due to the presence of a thick muscular sheath around the flagellum in 
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F146731BFC5EFA02" authorityName="Hyman, 2007 Semislug (Hyman" authorityYear="2007" box="[858,949,1392,1417]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Peloparion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="iridis">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F146731BFC5EFA02" box="[858,949,1392,1417]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">P. iridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In 
<taxonomicName id="2BBA39EDFFBE6A23F1FF731BFBB0FA02" box="[995,1115,1392,1417]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" genus="Peloparion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="helenae">
<emphasis id="DECE9E7CFFBE6A23F1FF731BFBB0FA02" box="[995,1115,1392,1417]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">P. helenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is due to the positioning of the cryptae, which are situated only in the distal end of the epiphallus. This corresponds to the presence of only a few short branching spines on the spermatophore around the base of the tail-pipe. The presence of cryptae, absence of an epiphallic caecum and extremely short vagina unite this genus with the southeast Australian group of helicarionid genera.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
